<TITLE> Gen Aye's visit will strengthen ties: CA </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 6 (bdnews24.com) -- Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed said Monday that the visit of Myanmar's second-in-command would further strengthen the relationship between Bangladesh and Myanmar. Myanmar's vice-senior General Maung Aye, with a delegation of ministers, will arrive in Dhaka on Tuesday on a three-day visit for bilateral talks. Myanmar ambassador in Dhaka U Phae Than and Fakhruddin met at the the Chief Adviser's Office ahead the visit Monday, the CA's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim said. "The visit of Myanmar's vice-senior General Maung Aye will make the relationship between the two countries stronger," Fahim Munaim quoted the CA as saying. Munaim said the CA hoped they would have talks with the Myanmar delegation to improve communication system and leasing of land during the visit. The Myanmar ambassador told the CA that his country had always given priority to having good relation with Bangladesh. The CA thanked the Myanmar government for its support to Bangladesh on various national and international issues. The Myanmar ambassador told the CA that general elections in Myanmar would be held in 2010. Myanmar's vice-senior general will lead a 55-member delegation with seven ministers and chief of air and naval forces of the country. bdnews
